<i>The cosplay club that Dad's 
been hanging out at...</i>

65
00:04:09.620 --> 00:04:11.750
<i>There was more stuff from 
there in the trash.</i>

66
00:04:12.800 --> 00:04:15.810
<i>He has been reckless with his money lately.</i>

67
00:04:16.330 --> 00:04:19.010
<i>But I have a nagging feeling 
that it's more than that.</i>

68
00:04:19.440 --> 00:04:21.430
<i>He's hiding something.</i>

69
00:04:21.430 --> 00:04:24.350
<i>If I asked him directly, I'm sure 
he'd just dodge the question.</i>

70
00:04:24.870 --> 00:04:26.670
<i>I need some evidence here!</i>

71
00:04:28.390 --> 00:04:31.930
Boy, searching this Internet 
sure is a pain, though!

72
00:04:31.930 --> 00:04:34.020
Maybe I should whip something up!

73
00:04:37.030 --> 00:04:39.390
I see, I see...

74
00:04:39.390 --> 00:04:41.520
This character is excellent!

75
00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:43.280
Another winner from Meiko-san!

76
00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:44.910
You're too kind!

77
00:04:44.910 --> 00:04:48.150
I'm about to head over to 
a TV network after this.

78
00:04:48.150 --> 00:04:49.280
Care to join me?

79
00:04:52.600 --> 00:04:55.420
A-A TV network, Kao-san!

80
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:56.660
What do we do?!

81
00:04:56.660 --> 00:04:58.280
What do you mean?

82
00:04:58.280 --> 00:05:01.800
We came here for work, so we need to go in!

83
00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:03.550
Hey, Gaya-san!

84
00:05:03.550 --> 00:05:04.530
What's going on?

85
00:05:04.530 --> 00:05:06.170
How've you been, man?!

86
00:05:06.170 --> 00:05:08.150
Hey! Y'know, I'm so sorry!

87
00:05:08.150 --> 00:05:10.620
I haven't had any time to call you!

88
00:05:11.340 --> 00:05:13.640
He's a producer at this network.

89
00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:16.840
He and I go way back.

90
00:05:16.840 --> 00:05:20.610
I mainly work on TV anime productions.

91
00:05:20.610 --> 00:05:23.670
If Gaya-san's scouted you out, 
I'd be happy to talk showbiz!

92
00:05:24.540 --> 00:05:26.100
T-TV anime!

93
00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:28.860
Th-This is a whole new level here...

94
00:05:28.860 --> 00:05:31.270
Is this the world of console ports?!

95
00:05:29.300 --> 00:05:31.270
Anime is great!

96
00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:36.560
But in the future, eroge could very 
well get turned into TV anime!

97
00:05:36.560 --> 00:05:38.430
And that could be us!

98
00:05:40.780 --> 00:05:42.760
We're back...

99
00:05:42.760 --> 00:05:45.450
That sure was mentally draining.

100
00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:49.260
Ah. Kaori-san, Meiko-san.

101
00:05:49.260 --> 00:05:50.620
Welcome back.

102
00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:52.760
Sounds like you girls 
are having a good time.

103
00:05:52.760 --> 00:05:54.330
What were you talking about?

104
00:05:54.330 --> 00:05:57.070
About <i>Kanon</i>, the game that just came out.

105
00:05:57.070 --> 00:05:58.520
It's really something else!

106
00:05:58.520 --> 00:06:01.360
I can't believe how unique the heroine is.

107
00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:04.710
Her trademark phrase is "uguu"! "Uguu"!

108
00:06:04.710 --> 00:06:06.710
I could understand "dayomon," at least!

109
00:06:07.530 --> 00:06:09.620
That almost reminds me of Kono-chan.

110
00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:10.790
I can see that.

111
00:06:10.790 --> 00:06:13.010
You don't know what she's going to say next,

112
00:06:13.010 --> 00:06:14.770
and she's got such a unique way of talking.

113
00:06:16.950 --> 00:06:20.390
It's still cold out when 
it gets this late...

114
00:06:21.770 --> 00:06:25.130
Is the manager really going to show up?

115
00:06:28.150 --> 00:06:33.660
Mamoru

116
00:06:28.150 --> 00:06:33.660
Dad should show
up at the club.
Let me know as
soon as you see
 him.

