Dad.

261
00:12:41.640 --> 00:12:44.060
You became the owner of that 
cosplay club, am I right?

262
00:12:44.740 --> 00:12:45.950
I looked it up.

263
00:12:46.420 --> 00:12:49.960
You took joint ownership with Ichigaya 
for a number of his businesses.

264
00:12:49.960 --> 00:12:53.050
You used company money for that, didn't you?

265
00:12:53.600 --> 00:12:56.420
You didn't raise the pay for any of us...

266
00:12:56.420 --> 00:12:58.430
How dare you spend it on that?!

267
00:12:58.430 --> 00:13:00.060
Shut up! Shut up!

268
00:13:00.060 --> 00:13:03.010
Don't talk back when all you 
do is make your little games!

269
00:13:03.010 --> 00:13:05.460
Are you the ones making the deals?

270
00:13:05.460 --> 00:13:07.220
Running the business?!

271
00:13:07.220 --> 00:13:10.630
Why do <i>you</i> get to have all 
the fun making games?!

272
00:13:10.980 --> 00:13:13.990
You guys get all the damn credit!

273
00:13:13.990 --> 00:13:15.910
I'm the president of this company!

274
00:13:15.910 --> 00:13:17.280
When do I...

275
00:13:17.280 --> 00:13:20.270
When do <i>I</i> get to do something great?!

276
00:13:24.250 --> 00:13:27.650
Have any of you heard 
about dot-com companies?

277
00:13:27.650 --> 00:13:31.630
It's never been a better time 
for American IT companies!

278
00:13:31.630 --> 00:13:34.430
Which is why it's the perfect 
time for me and Ichigaya

279
00:13:34.430 --> 00:13:38.430
to start a new company in the US that 
combines the Internet and video games!

280
00:13:38.430 --> 00:13:40.290
This is gonna be real big!

281
00:13:40.290 --> 00:13:41.900
Excuse me, everyone.

282
00:13:41.900 --> 00:13:42.510
Huh?

283
00:13:42.510 --> 00:13:45.320
Please excuse my interruption.

284
00:13:45.320 --> 00:13:47.750
If I could ask you all to 
come to the conference room.

285
00:13:47.750 --> 00:13:49.650
I'm sorry, Hashimoto-san.

286
00:13:49.650 --> 00:13:50.940
Now's not the time for—

287
00:13:50.320 --> 00:13:51.550
This is an urgent matter.

288
00:13:52.260 --> 00:13:54.950
Ichigaya-san has been arrested.

289
00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:58.880
Game creator Hikaru 
Ichigaya has been arrested

290
00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:59.400
Tokyo
Diamond Studio

291
00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:59.400
Suspect Hikaru Ichigaya 
Arrested on scene today

292
00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:59.400
Breaking News

293
00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:59.400
Renowned game creator suspected of fraud
Approached multiple individuals with startup offers

294
00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:01.440
on suspected charges of massive fraud.

295
00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:04.990
Arrested for alleged fraud

296
00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:04.990
Suspect Hikaru Ichigaya (37), game creator

297
00:14:01.440 --> 00:14:05.000
Ichigaya is charged with colluding with 
those in the television industry.

298
00:14:04.990 --> 00:14:11.490
Total losses may exceed three billion yen

299
00:14:05.000 --> 00:14:08.940
He is said to have approached multiple 
individuals with false startup business offers,

300
00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:11.500
and fraudulently soliciting 
investments from them.

301
00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:15.330
The total losses are estimated 
to exceed three billion yen.

302
00:14:15.330 --> 00:14:24.180
Ichigaya, a renowned game creator known 
for the hit 1987 series, <i>Fire Dragon</i>,

303
00:14:24.180 --> 00:14:28.430
is believed to have been facing 
financial trouble in recent years...

304
00:14:24.820 --> 00:14:27.930
They arrested Ichigaya-san...

305
00:14:27.930 --> 00:14:29.000
What?!

306
00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:31.200
What's going on here?!

307
00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:32.350
Manager.

308
00:14:32.350 --> 00:14:34.820
He suckered you out of your money.

309
00:14:36.690 --> 00:14:38.940
Th-This is some sort of prank.

310
00:14:38.940 --> 00:14:40.510
It must be a misunderstanding.

311
00:14:40.510 --> 00:14:42.600
He would never lie to me.

312
00:14:42.600 --> 00:14:44.400
He said that we were...

313
00:14:44.400 --> 00:14:45.360
Dad.

314
00:14:45.770 --> 00:14:47.640
He was stringing you along.

315
00:14:58.630 --> 00:15:00.210
Oh, brother.

316
00:15:01.810 --> 00:15:03.340
Give it back...

317
00:15:03.840 --> 00:15:05.810
Give it back...

318
00:15:05.810 --> 00:15:07.250
My one billion...

319
00:15:07.460 --> 00:15:08.090
What?

320
00:15:09.800 --> 00:15:12.750
O-One billion?!

321
00:15:17.610 --> 00:15:20.710
<i>With the manager a scam victim 
in an investment fraud scheme,</i>

322
00:15:20.710 --> 00:15:26.440
<i>Alcohol Soft suddenly found themselves 
one billion yen in debt.</i>

323
00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.280
Kao-san!

324
00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:42.950
I just came back from Ichigaya's 
Diamond Studio office.

325
00:15:43.340 --> 00:15:45.560
It was swarming with debt 
collectors and policemen,

326
00:15:45.560 --> 00:15:47.460
so I didn't manage to get anything back.

327
00:15:50.470 --> 00:15:52.790
Maybe it's time we closed up shop.

328
00:15:58.860 --> 00:16:04.060
In the end, Ichigaya was no better than 
a scummy eroge company president.

329
00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:08.950
Nothing but big talk, while 
never showing up for work.

330
00:16:08.950 --> 00:16:12.800
If only the manager had been 
content with humbly making games.

331
00:16:12.800 --> 00:16:15.750
Having a hit title on his hands 
completely messed up his life.

332
00:16:18.250 --> 00:16:23.200
If we had taken a step back, we could 
have realized something was wrong.

333
00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:25.770
But we all bought it hook, line, and sinker.

334
00:16:25.770 --> 00:16:26.910
Well, come on!

335
00:16:26.910 --> 00:16:29.210
Who wouldn't want to see 
their game on console?!

336
00:16:29.210 --> 00:16:30.390
I'm sorry.

337
00:16:30.390 --> 00:16:31.800
I wasn't thinking clearly...

338
00:16:31.800 --> 00:16:34.000
You're not to blame at all, Mei-chan!

339
00:16:34.240 --> 00:16:36.890
Treating us like your personal wallet!

340
00:16:36.890 --> 00:16:39.070
He won't get away with this!

341
00:16:39.070 --> 00:16:40.100
Um...

342
00:16:40.880 --> 00:16:42.270
Kono-chan.

343
00:16:42.270 --> 00:16:46.320
Does this mean you're not 
going to make games anymore?

344
00:16:48.210 --> 00:16:50.300
I'll still make games.

345
00:16:51.520 --> 00:16:52.520
Only...

346
00:16:54.310 --> 00:16:56.520
it may not be at this company.

347
00:18:58.770 --> 00:19:00.140
Mamoru-kun!

348
00:19:00.140 --> 00:19:02.210
You're still here, huh?

349
00:19:02.210 --> 00:19:05.320
Well, the development room 
is where I've been sleeping.

350
00:19:06.430 --> 00:19:08.830
Dad was hospitalized from 
the shock of it all.

351
00:19:09.110 --> 00:19:10.370
Makes you laugh, doesn't it?

352
00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:13.260
He's never had an ounce of business sense.

353
00:19:13.980 --> 00:19:16.720
One billion yen...

354
00:19:19.260 --> 00:19:23.160
Opening a computer shop after mass 
retailers started carrying them.

355
00:19:23.160 --> 00:19:27.340
Starting a game company, despite never 
really having played a video game.

356
00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:31.280
I knew all of this, but I let 
him be, so maybe I'm no better.

357
00:19:33.710 --> 00:19:37.510
Was there really nothing 
more I could have done?

358
00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:39.330
You did plenty.

359
00:19:39.330 --> 00:19:40.790
You even tracked him down.

360
00:19:41.280 --> 00:19:42.400
Still!

361
00:19:42.400 --> 00:19:45.530
I came back in time again, but 
I was powerless to do anything...

362
00:19:45.950 --> 00:19:47.730
It's just too awful!

363
00:19:48.270 --> 00:19:50.220
I had a hunch that something was wrong.

364
00:19:50.220 --> 00:19:53.250
When someone from the future like 
you had no idea who Ichigaya was.

365
00:19:53.590 --> 00:19:56.260
Mamoru-kun, who's that?

366
00:19:56.620 --> 00:19:59.070
I didn't take things seriously.

367
00:19:59.070 --> 00:20:02.250
I had second thoughts about 
believing what you said.

368
00:20:02.600 --> 00:20:03.490
However...

369
00:20:04.310 --> 00:20:07.090
I might have been able 
to prevent all of this.

370
00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:09.110
And even if I couldn't,

371
00:20:09.110 --> 00:20:11.950
I could have at least paid 
attention to what Dad was up to.

372
00:20:13.240 --> 00:20:17.080
If I had done that, maybe I could 
have kept everyone's dream alive.

373
00:20:17.560 --> 00:20:19.410
Everyone's dream?

374
00:20:19.410 --> 00:20:22.370
Mamoru-kun, you think this is your fault?

375
00:20:22.750 --> 00:20:23.860
Maybe it wasn't.

376
00:20:24.310 --> 00:20:27.050
But I can't deny I was a 
little too unsuspecting.

377
00:20:27.050 --> 00:20:31.290
Mamoru-kun, you love Alcohol 
Soft deep down, don't you?

378
00:20:31.290 --> 00:20:32.250
Not really.

379
00:20:32.500 --> 00:20:33.380
I've been...

380
00:20:34.850 --> 00:20:36.400
just stuck here the whole time.

381
00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:51.020
Mamoru-kun!

382
00:20:51.670 --> 00:20:53.320
Let's make a game!

383
00:20:53.320 --> 00:20:55.680
I'll do the art, so let's make a game!

384
00:20:55.680 --> 00:20:58.700
We'll use it to save the company!

385
00:21:00.210 --> 00:21:01.110
Ugh...

386
00:21:01.110 --> 00:21:02.280
Hey!

387
00:21:02.280 --> 00:21:06.390
This is the part where you go 
all whammo, then "yeahhhh"!

388
00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:08.550
What's with the "ugh"?!

389
00:21:10.010 --> 00:21:14.350
I've always wanted to make a game 
with everyone at Alcohol Soft!

390
00:21:14.350 --> 00:21:18.250
I knew if I was going to make a game, 
I wanted it to be with all of you!

391
00:21:18.540 --> 00:21:20.540
But I couldn't say it...

392
00:21:20.540 --> 00:21:23.060
I was too afraid of changing the past.

393
00:21:23.540 --> 00:21:24.550
But still!

394
00:21:24.550 --> 00:21:27.910
If we don't use my powers now, then when?!

395
00:21:27.910 --> 00:21:30.180
The game I've always wanted to make!

396
00:21:30.180 --> 00:21:33.820
I know that I want to make 
it right here, right now!

397
00:21:34.180 --> 00:21:35.220
Ugh...

398
00:21:35.220 --> 00:21:35.930
What?!

399
00:21:35.930 --> 00:21:37.280
"Ugh" again?!

400
00:21:37.610 --> 00:21:40.170
I can't deny that your drawing was amazing.

401
00:21:40.980 --> 00:21:43.420
To be honest, it feels 
straight out of the future.

402
00:21:44.560 --> 00:21:46.980
But what can you do with just drawings?!

403
00:21:46.980 --> 00:21:48.900
We're talking one billion yen! One billion!

404
00:21:50.390 --> 00:21:52.950
You can't possibly make one 
billion yen off an eroge...

405
00:21:55.440 --> 00:21:59.870
Mamoru-kun, you still don't 
understand the power of bishojo.

406
00:22:00.710 --> 00:22:03.670
Bishojo has way more power than you think!

407
00:22:03.670 --> 00:22:05.710
As someone from the future, I guarantee it!

408
00:22:05.710 --> 00:22:08.220
Besides, I'm not alone!

409
00:22:08.220 --> 00:22:12.810
Everyone at Alcohol Soft believes 
in the power of bishojo!

410
00:22:12.810 --> 00:22:15.980
If we all work together, 
nothing's impossible!

411
00:22:15.980 --> 00:22:18.940
The other day, I helped out a boy I met,

412
00:22:18.940 --> 00:22:20.640
because he was in trouble!

413
00:22:20.640 --> 00:22:23.720
It doesn't matter whether
I change the past or future!

414
00:22:23.720 --> 00:22:27.170
I want to do whatever I can, right now!

415
00:22:27.170 --> 00:22:30.020
Mamoru-kun, are you fine 
with just giving up?!

416
00:22:30.020 --> 00:22:32.660
Are you fine with losing everything?!

417
00:22:32.660 --> 00:22:34.500
I don't think you are!

418
00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:39.040
I know all too well that your heart 
is burning with passion deep down!

419
00:22:39.040 --> 00:22:40.010
So please!

420
00:22:40.010 --> 00:22:41.760
Believe in me!

421
00:22:41.760 --> 00:22:42.880
Mamoru-kun!

422
00:22:47.920 --> 00:22:49.110
Can you do it?

423
00:22:50.040 --> 00:22:53.800
Can you really make that amazing of a game?

424
00:22:53.800 --> 00:22:54.900
I can!

425
00:22:54.900 --> 00:22:58.130
I'm going to make the 
ultimate game, right here!

426
00:22:59.400 --> 00:23:01.120
Then have it your way.

427
00:23:02.390 --> 00:23:05.900
Whatever you want to make, 
I'll bring it to life.

428
00:23:06.630 --> 00:23:09.220
So make the game that you want!

429
00:23:09.220 --> 00:23:11.370
You can leave the programming to me!

430
00:23:11.370 --> 00:23:13.150
Really? Whatever I want?

431
00:23:13.150 --> 00:23:14.000
Yeah.

432
00:23:14.380 --> 00:23:15.620
You name it!

433
00:23:16.380 --> 00:23:18.780
You mean I can activate beast mode?!

434
00:23:18.780 --> 00:23:20.400
What the heck is beast mode?

435
00:23:20.400 --> 00:23:24.980
Um, beast mode is when, 
well, you go all out!

436
00:23:24.980 --> 00:23:26.120
Sure, whatever.

437
00:23:27.370 --> 00:23:28.510
Do it!

438
00:23:28.510 --> 00:23:29.730
Go beast mode!

439
00:23:31.270 --> 00:23:32.670
All right!

440
00:23:34.980 --> 00:23:40.060
HELP for help

441
